# React Native Standards

## API Calls — Use `fetchAPI` (MANDATORY)

All HTTP requests MUST use `fetchAPI` from `@/lib/fetch`. Never use raw `fetch()`.

`fetchAPI` provides: auto JWT injection, 401 token refresh, retry logic, centralized error handling.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — raw fetch, no auth, no retry, no error handling
const res = await fetch(`${API_URL}/ride/history`);
const data = await res.json();

// ✅ GOOD — fetchAPI handles auth, retries, and errors
import { fetchAPI } from "@/lib/fetch";
const { data } = await fetchAPI("/(api)/ride/history");
```

## Component Structure

```tsx
interface BookingCardProps {
  booking: Booking;
  onPress: (id: string) => void;
}

export const BookingCard: React.FC<BookingCardProps> = ({ booking, onPress }) => (
  <Pressable onPress={() => onPress(booking.id)}>
    <Text>{booking.destination}</Text>
  </Pressable>
);
```

## State Management

```tsx
// ❌ BAD - Direct state mutation
user.name = 'New Name';

// ✅ GOOD - Immutable update
setUser(prev => ({ ...prev, name: 'New Name' }));
```

## Required Practices

- Use NativeWind (Tailwind) for styling
- Platform-specific code with `Platform.select`
- Handle keyboard avoiding views
- Implement pull-to-refresh
- Add loading and error states
- Optimize FlatList with `getItemLayout`
- Icons: use `<Image source={icons.xxx} />` with PNG assets from `constants/index.ts`
